{
  "stem": "20686.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And I think what-- what I feel, in particular in this situation, that a man who is condemned to die in this-- he has the right to choose his death.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And what he did, he deprived us of the choice.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because if we knew what's going on, I'm sure that the people would stand-- stand up against the Germans with-- with their fist, with-- with-- with nothing.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "With-- with-- they would stand up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Of course, they would-- we would be slaughtered.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But he-- he took away this right from us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And because Germany, not the Nazis, but Germany, was interested to have this murder done orderly, they needed a man like him, who will keep the secret, who will prepare transport after transport to be sent away to be exterminated.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They conducted lists, and they had a more-or-less idea, who is still-- can be used for work.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he-- he constantly kept us-- he told us constantly that we're going out to work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But how can a sane person [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] believe that a three-year-old child is sent out to work?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think it-- I think you've got to be really sort of-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Either this is such-- it such a cynicism.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How can one believe that a man who got two days to live that he's going to-- he's going to-- he's taking out to-- to work?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was obvious.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Yet, he-- he kept denying.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when a-- when a human being is about to die, and you leave him the slightest gap of hope, he'll-- he'll believe you.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's what the Germans did.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Before entering the gas chambers, they gave you a piece of soap and a towel, so you can dry yourself.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
